Class TryParse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.robtimus.tryparse.TryParse

  • public final class TryParse
extends Object
    Provides functionality to parse to Optional and its primitive versions.

      • tryParseInt

        @NativeParsing
public static OptionalInt tryParseInt(CharSequence cs)
        Tries to parse the given CharSequence. This method is a special case of tryParseInt(CharSequence, int) using radix 10.
        Parameters:
        cs - The CharSequence to parse.
        Returns:
        An OptionalInt with the result of parsing the given portion of the given CharSequence, or OptionalInt.empty() if parsing failed.

      • tryParseInt

        @NativeParsing
public static OptionalInt tryParseInt(CharSequence cs,
                                                      int radix)
        Tries to parse the given CharSequence. This method is like Integer.parseInt but instead of throwing a NumberFormatException it will return an empty OptionalInt.
        Parameters:
        cs - The CharSequence to parse.
        radix - The radix to use, between Character.MIN_RADIX and Character.MAX_RADIX inclusive.
        Returns:
        An OptionalInt with the result of parsing the given portion of the given CharSequence, or OptionalInt.empty() if parsing failed.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given radix is invalid.

      • tryParseInt

        @NativeParsing
public static OptionalInt tryParseInt(CharSequence cs,
                                                      int start,
                                                      int end)
        Tries to parse the portion of the given CharSequence from the given start and end indexes. This method is a special case of tryParseInt(CharSequence, int, int, int) using radix 10.
        Parameters:
        cs - The CharSequence to parse.
        start - The index in the CharSequence to start parsing, inclusive.
        end - The index in the CharSequence to end parsing, exclusive.
        Returns:
        An OptionalInt with the result of parsing the given portion of the given CharSequence, or OptionalInt.empty() if parsing failed.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the given start index is negative or larger than the given end index, or if the given end index is larger than the given CharSequence's length.

      • tryParseBoolean

        @NativeParsing
public static Optional<Boolean> tryParseBoolean(CharSequence cs)
        Tries to parse the portion of the given CharSequence from the given start and end indexes. Unlike Boolean.parseBoolean(String), this method does not return false for any value that is not "true". Instead, it returns an empty Optional for any value that is not "true" or "false" case insensitively.
        Parameters:
        cs - The CharSequence to parse.
        Returns:
        An Optional with the result of parsing the given portion of the given CharSequence, or Optional.empty() if parsing failed.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the given start index is negative or larger than the given end index, or if the given end index is larger than the given CharSequence's length.

        Parameters:

      • tryParse

        @ExceptionBasedParsing
public static <T,R> Optional<R> tryParse(T input,
                                                                 ParseFunction<? super T,? extends R,? extends Exception> parser)
        Tries to parse an object. This is a generic purpose method that will attempt to parse the given input using the given parser. If the parsing throws any exception, this method will return Optional.empty() instead.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of object to parse.
        R - The type of the parse result.
        Parameters:
        input - The object to parse.
        parser - The parser that will perform the parsing.
        Returns:
        An Optional with the result of parsing the given object, or Optional.empty() if parsing failed with an exception, or if the parser returned null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given parser is null, or if the given input is null and the parser does not accept null values.
        Since:
        1.1

      • tryParse

        @ExceptionBasedParsing
public static <T,R,X extends Exception> Optional<R> tryParse(T input,
                                                                                     ParseFunction<? super T,? extends R,? extends X> parser,
                                                                                     Class<X> expectedExceptionType)
        Tries to parse an object. This is a generic purpose method that will attempt to parse the given input using the given parser. If the parsing throws an exception of the given expected exception type, this method will return Optional.empty() instead. Any other (unchecked) exceptions will be thrown as-is.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of object to parse.
        R - The type of the parse result.
        X - The type of exception that occurs if parsing fails.
        Parameters:
        input - The object to parse.
        parser - The parser that will perform the parsing.
        expectedExceptionType - The expected type of exception.
        Returns:
        An Optional with the result of parsing the given object, or Optional.empty() if parsing failed with the given exception type, or if the parser returned null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given parser or expected exception type is null, or if the given input is null and the parser does not accept null values.
        Since:
        1.1
